of the bilaminar germ disc","Formation of the primitive streak","Genesis of the amniotic cavity","Formation of the trophoblast lacunae","Development of the secondary yolk sac"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EAt day 9 post-fertilisation, \u003Cstrong\u003Etrophoblast lacunae form\u003C/strong\u003E within the syncytiotrophoblast layer. These spaces will eventually become the intervillous spaces of the placenta where maternal blood flows.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options occur at different times:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDevelopment of the bilaminar germ disc\u003C/strong\u003E occurs around day 8\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFormation of the primitive streak\u003C/strong\u003E occurs around day 15\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGenesis of the amniotic cavity\u003C/strong\u003E begins around day 8\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDevelopment of the secondary yolk sac\u003C/strong\u003E occurs around day 12\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe formation of trophoblast lacunae is a crucial step in early placental development, preceding the establishment of maternal blood flow into the developing placenta.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["At day 9 of embryological development, trophoblast lacunae form as spaces within the syncytiotrophoblast layer.","Trophoblast lacunae are precursors to the intervillous spaces of the placenta.","The formation of trophoblast lacunae precedes maternal blood flow into the developing placenta."],"references":["Padubidri, V. G., \u0026 Daftary, S. N. (Eds.). (2014). Shaw\u0027s Textbook of Gynecology E-book. Elsevier health sciences","Singh, V. (2022). Textbook of clinical embryology, -E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"